{
  "texts": [
    "Third, although we investigated a quantitative and verbal ability test, these were specific tests that each consisted of a single type of item.",
    "LLMs may perform better or worse on different item types, and there are many item types that we did not explore.",
    "For example, matrix reasoning items (e.g., Raven's standard progressive matrices) are commonly used, yet using an LLM on such items would require a multimodal LLM that can accept images as inputs.",
    "Initial evidence suggests that LLMs score well on matrix reasoning items when they are translated into text-based questions (Webb et al., 2023).",
    "Future work could investigate additional item types in validated tests used for high-stakes selection."
  ]
}